task.summary: Firebase cloud messaging and auth, plus some refactor and introduction of first real units tests.
Refactor for better ProtoBuf command handling. More unit tests. Mocking USB live device tests.
Use a background services to manage the USB connections and use broadcast IPC to commnucate with UX.
Refactor USB and Firebase Cloud Messaging services to better use background services and binding to separate concerns.
Get the latest changes debugged on physical Android hardware. Also refactored the Usb classes so that one is more device-oriented and the other is more device manager oriented.

Support the application launching when the user plugs in (or reboots) the MCU-based USB device. Break up the USB background processor into a BroadcastReceiver (short-lived for USB events) and a Service for long-running support of USB bytes.
Clean up the USB disconnect/reconnect code to be a bit more robust.

Robot is rolling again (since the rewrite to android) Upgraded to protobuf 3.0.0 (real instead of nano) Cleaned up libs Handle different device IDs for motors Handle the VCU commands as a set of MCU commands to the vehicle firmware via USB.
Complete the chain of VCU to MCU commands to get the robot rolling again!
